Urizen and what he called "single vision and Newton's sleep".<br />
(http://home.earthlink.net/~lrgoldner/renaissance.html)
<br /><br />
</ref>
In any case, this cosmobiological tradition is an 'alternative strand of modernity', 
which lost out but could perhaps be retrieved and redeveloped.

Other important genealogies to recreate a participatory worldview appropriate to our age have
